#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:15
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr "動機"

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:17
msgid ""
"The primary motivation for this RFC is to work out the stabilization of the "
"`c_str` and `c_vec` modules. Both of these modules exist for interoperating "
"with C types to ensure that values can cross the boundary of Rust and C "
"relatively safely. These types also need to be designed with ergonomics in "
"mind to ensure that it's tough to get them wrong and easy to get them right."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:23
msgid ""
"The current `CString` and `CVec` types are quite old and are long due for a "
"scrutinization, and these types are currently serving a number of competing "
"concerns:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:27
msgid ""
"A `CString` can both take ownership of a pointer as well as inspect a "
"pointer."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:29
msgid "A `CString` is always allocated/deallocated on the libc heap."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:30
msgid "A `CVec` looks like a slice but does not quite act like one."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:31
msgid "A `CString` looks like a byte slice but does not quite act like one."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:32
msgid ""
"There are a number of pieces of duplicated functionality throughout the "
"standard library when dealing with raw C types. There are a number of "
"conversion functions on the `Vec` and `String` types as well as the `str` "
"and `slice` modules."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:37
msgid ""
"In general all of this functionality needs to be reconciled with one another "
"to provide a consistent and coherence interface when operating with types "
"originating from C."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:41
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr "詳細設計"

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:43
msgid ""
"In refactoring all usage could be categorized into one of three categories:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:45
msgid "A Rust type wants to be passed into C."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:46
msgid "A C type was handed to Rust, but Rust does not own it."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:47
msgid "A C type was handed to Rust, and Rust owns it."
msgstr ""

#: src/0494-c_str-and-c_vec-stability.md:49
msgid ""
"The current `CString` attempts to handle all three of these concerns all at "
"once, somewhat conflating desires. Additionally, `CVec` provides a fairly "
"different interface than `CString` while providing similar functionality."
msgstr ""

